#. <section class="sutta" id="mn54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn54:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 54"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 54"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn54:0.2"
msgid "Potaliyasutta"
msgstr "With Potaliya the Wanderer"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn54:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅguttarāpesu viharati āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅguttarāpānaṃ "
"nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Northern Āpaṇas, near "
"the town of theirs named Āpaṇa."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āpaṇaṃ piṇḍāya "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Āpaṇa for alms."

msgctxt "mn54:2.2"
msgid ""
"Āpaṇe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yenaññataro "
"vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya."
msgstr ""
"He wandered for alms in Āpaṇa. After the meal, on his return from alms-"
"round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation."

#. VAR: ajjhogāhetvā → ajjhogahetvā (bj, s1-3, km) | ajjhogāhitvā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the "
"day’s meditation."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. VAR: chattupāhanāhi → chattupāhano (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:3.1"
msgid ""
"Potaliyopi kho gahapati sampannanivāsanapāvuraṇo chattupāhanāhi "
"jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena so vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Potaliya the householder also approached that forest grove while going for a "
"walk. He was well dressed in a cloak and sarong, with parasol and sandals. "
"Having plunged deep into it, he went up to the Buddha, and exchanged "
"greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn54:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ "
"ṭhitaṃ kho potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, "
"and the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "mn54:3.3"
msgid "“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti."
msgstr "“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”"
"ti kupito anattamano tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr ""
"When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic "
"Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he stayed silent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.360"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:3.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "mn54:3.6"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and a third time the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "mn54:3.7"
msgid "“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti."
msgstr "“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.8"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”"
"ti kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic "
"Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn54:3.9"
msgid ""
"“tayidaṃ, bho gotama, nacchannaṃ, tayidaṃ nappatirūpaṃ, yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ "
"gahapativādena samudācarasī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, it is neither proper nor appropriate for you to address me "
"as ‘householder’.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.10"
msgid ""
"“Te hi te, gahapati, ākārā, te liṅgā, te nimittā yathā taṃ gahapatissā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well, householder, you have the features, attributes, and signs of a "
"householder.”"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-nuances-of-vohara/4136
msgctxt "mn54:3.11"
msgid ""
"“Tathā hi pana me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā "
"samucchinnā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, it’s because I have refused all work and cut off all "
"judgments.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.12"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, gahapati, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā "
"samucchinnā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Householder, in what way have you refused all work and cut off all "
"judgments?”"

# me … yam ahosi + “what I used to have”
msgctxt "mn54:3.13"
msgid ""
"“Idha me, bho gotama, yaṃ ahosi dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā "
"sabbaṃ taṃ puttānaṃ dāyajjaṃ niyyātaṃ, tatthāhaṃ anovādī anupavādī "
"ghāsacchādanaparamo viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, all the money, grain, gold, and silver I used to have has "
"been handed over to my children as their inheritance. And in this matter I "
"do not advise or reprimand them, but live with nothing more than food and "
"clothes."

#. VAR: Evaṃ kho me → evañca me (s1-3) | evaṃ me (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:3.14"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā "
"samucchinnā”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I have refused all work and cut off all judgments.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.15"
msgid ""
"“Aññathā kho tvaṃ, gahapati, vohārasamucchedaṃ vadasi, aññathā ca pana "
"ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The cutting off of judgments as you describe it is one thing, householder, "
"but the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training is quite "
"different.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.16"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hoti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what, sir, is cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training?"

msgctxt "mn54:3.17"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye "
"vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti."
msgstr "Sir, please teach me this.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.18"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn54:3.19"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:4.1"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. VAR: me → yeme pana (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:4.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭha kho ime, gahapati, dhammā ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, these eight things lead to the cutting off of judgments in the "
"noble one’s training."

msgctxt "mn54:4.3"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "mn54:4.4"
msgid "Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo;"
msgstr ""
"Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living "
"creatures."

msgctxt "mn54:4.5"
msgid "dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabbaṃ;"
msgstr "Stealing should be given up, relying on not stealing."

#. VAR: saccavācaṃ → saccaṃ vācaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:4.6"
msgid "saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo;"
msgstr "Lying should be given up, relying on speaking the truth."

msgctxt "mn54:4.7"
msgid "apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā;"
msgstr ""
"Divisive speech should be given up, relying on speech that isn’t divisive."

msgctxt "mn54:4.8"
msgid "agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo;"
msgstr ""
"Greed and lust should be given up, relying on not being greedy and lustful."

msgctxt "mn54:4.9"
msgid "anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo;"
msgstr ""
"Blaming and insulting should be given up, relying on not blaming and not "
"insulting."

msgctxt "mn54:4.10"
msgid "akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo;"
msgstr ""
"Anger and distress should be given up, relying on not being angry and "
"distressed."

msgctxt "mn54:4.11"
msgid "anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo."
msgstr "Arrogance should be given up, relying on not being arrogant."

#. VAR: vitthārena → vitthāretvā (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:4.12"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, gahapati, aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena avibhattā, "
"ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the eight things—stated in brief without being analyzed in detail—"
"that lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye me, bhante, bhagavatā aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena "
"avibhattā, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti, sādhu me, bhante, "
"bhagavā ime aṭṭha dhamme vitthārena vibhajatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, please teach me these eight things in detail out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "mn54:5.2"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn54:5.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya."

msgctxt "mn54:5.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.361"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:6.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, "
"kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"“‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living "
"creatures.’ That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn54:6.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "mn54:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu pāṇātipātī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""
"‘I am practicing to give up and cut off the fetters that might cause me to "
"kill living creatures."

#. VAR: Ahañceva → ahañce (?)
#. VAR: anuviccāpi maṃ viññū → anuvicca viññū (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:6.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana pāṇātipātī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya pāṇātipātapaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ pāṇātipātapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā pāṇātipātapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to kill living creatures, because of that I would reprimand "
"myself; sensible people, after examination, would criticize me; and when my "
"body breaks up, after death, I could expect to be reborn in a bad place."

msgctxt "mn54:6.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ pāṇātipāto."
msgstr "And killing living creatures is itself a fetter and a hindrance."

msgctxt "mn54:6.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca pāṇātipātapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, pāṇātipātā "
"paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""
"The distressing and feverish defilements that might arise because of killing "
"living creatures do not occur in someone who does not kill living creatures.’"

msgctxt "mn54:6.7"
msgid "‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living "
"creatures.’"

msgctxt "mn54:6.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:7.1"
msgid ""
"‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, "
"kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Stealing …"

msgctxt "mn54:7.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu adinnādāyī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana adinnādāyī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya adinnādānapaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ adinnādānapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā adinnādānapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ adinnādānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca adinnādānapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā adinnādānā "
"paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.7"
msgid "‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:7.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.362"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:8.1"
msgid ""
"‘Saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ "
"paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "lying …"

msgctxt "mn54:8.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu musāvādī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana musāvādī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya musāvādapaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ musāvādapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"duggati pāṭikaṅkhā musāvādapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ musāvādo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca musāvādapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, musāvādā "
"paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.7"
msgid "‘Saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:8.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:9.1"
msgid ""
"‘Apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, "
"kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "divisive speech …"

msgctxt "mn54:9.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu pisuṇavāco assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana pisuṇavāco assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya pisuṇavācāpaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ pisuṇavācāpaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā pisuṇavācāpaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ pisuṇā vācā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca pisuṇavācāpaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, pisuṇāya vācāya "
"paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.7"
msgid "‘Apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:9.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:10.1"
msgid ""
"‘Agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, "
"kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "greed and lust …"

msgctxt "mn54:10.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu giddhilobhī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana giddhilobhī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya "
"giddhilobhapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ giddhilobhapaccayā, "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā giddhilobhapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ giddhilobho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca giddhilobhapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, giddhilobhā "
"paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.7"
msgid "‘Agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:10.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.363"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:11.1"
msgid ""
"‘Anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ "
"paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "blaming and insulting …"

msgctxt "mn54:11.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu nindārosī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana nindārosī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya nindārosapaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ nindārosapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"duggati pāṭikaṅkhā nindārosapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ nindāroso."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca nindārosapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, anindārosissa "
"evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.7"
msgid "‘Anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:11.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:12.1"
msgid ""
"‘Akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, "
"kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "anger and distress …"

msgctxt "mn54:12.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu kodhūpāyāsī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana kodhūpāyāsī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya "
"kodhūpāyāsapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ kodhūpāyāsapaccayā, "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā kodhūpāyāsapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ kodhūpāyāso."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kodhūpāyāsapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, akkodhūpāyāsissa "
"evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.7"
msgid "‘Akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:12.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:13.1"
msgid ""
"‘Anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ "
"paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"Arrogance should be given up, relying on not being arrogant.’ That’s what I "
"said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn54:13.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "mn54:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu atimānī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""
"‘I am practicing to give up and cut off the fetters that might cause me to "
"be arrogant."

msgctxt "mn54:13.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana atimānī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya atimānapaccayā, "
"anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ atimānapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"duggati pāṭikaṅkhā atimānapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to be arrogant, because of that I would reprimand myself; "
"sensible people, after examination, would criticize me; and when my body "
"breaks up, after death, I could expect to be reborn in a bad place."

msgctxt "mn54:13.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ atimāno."
msgstr "And arrogance is itself a fetter and a hindrance."

msgctxt "mn54:13.6"
msgid ""
"Ye ca atimānapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, anatimānissa evaṃsa "
"te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’."
msgstr ""
"The distressing and feverish defilements that might arise because of "
"arrogance do not occur in someone who is not arrogant.’"

msgctxt "mn54:13.7"
msgid "‘Anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr "‘Arrogance should be given up by not being arrogant.’"

msgctxt "mn54:13.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.364"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: vibhattā → avibhattā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:14.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, gahapati, aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena vibhattā, ye "
"ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti;"
msgstr ""
"These are the eight things—stated in brief and analyzed in detail—that lead "
"to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training."

msgctxt "mn54:14.2"
msgid ""
"na tveva tāva ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ "
"vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But just this much does not constitute the cutting off of judgments in each "
"and every respect in the noble one’s training.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:14.3"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ "
"vohārasamucchedo hoti?"
msgstr ""
"“But, sir, how is there the cutting off of judgments in each and every "
"respect in the noble one’s training?"

msgctxt "mn54:14.4"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye sabbena "
"sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti."
msgstr "Sir, please teach me this.”"

msgctxt "mn54:14.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn54:14.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya."

msgctxt "mn54:14.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn54:14.8"
msgid "1. Kāmādīnavakathā"
msgstr "1. The Dangers of Sensual Pleasures"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, gahapati, kukkuro jighacchādubbalyapareto goghātakasūnaṃ "
"paccupaṭṭhito assa."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, suppose a dog weak with hunger was hanging around a butcher’s "
"shop."

#. VAR: upasumbheyya → upacchubheyya (bj, pts1) | upacchūbheyya (s1-3, km) | upaccumbheyya (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:15.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ "
"nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ lohitamakkhitaṃ upasumbheyya."
msgstr ""
"Then an expert butcher or their apprentice would toss them a skeleton "
"scraped clean of flesh and smeared in blood."

msgctxt "mn54:15.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "mn54:15.4"
msgid ""
"api nu kho so kukkuro amuṃ aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ "
"lohitamakkhitaṃ palehanto jighacchādubbalyaṃ paṭivineyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Gnawing on such a fleshless skeleton, would that dog still get rid of its "
"hunger?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:15.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:15.6"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why not?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:15.7"
msgid ""
"“Aduñhi, bhante, aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ "
"lohitamakkhitaṃ."
msgstr "Because that skeleton is scraped clean of flesh and smeared in blood."

msgctxt "mn54:15.8"
msgid "Yāvadeva pana so kukkuro kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti."
msgstr "That dog will eventually get weary and frustrated.”"

msgctxt "mn54:15.9"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "“In the same way, a noble disciple reflects:"

#. VAR: bahupāyāsā → bahūpāyāsā (bj, s2, s3, km)
msgctxt "mn54:15.10"
msgid ""
"‘aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘With the simile of a skeleton the Buddha said that sensual pleasures give "
"little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the "
"more full of drawbacks.’"

msgctxt "mn54:15.11"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā "
"taṃ abhinivajjetvā, yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso "
"lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""
"Having truly seen this with proper understanding, they reject equanimity "
"based on diversity and develop only the equanimity based on unity, where all "
"kinds of grasping to the world’s carnal delights cease without anything left "
"over."

# In the similar passage at SN 19, we find kāka, crow, instead of kaṅka, heron. Given the behavior described here, I think it’s likely the original was, in fact, crow. The Chinese parallel at MN 203 does indeed have 烏, crow, here. Comm. is silent.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: uḍḍīyeyya → uḍḍayeyya (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:16.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gijjho vā kaṅko vā kulalo vā maṃsapesiṃ ādāya "
"uḍḍīyeyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a vulture or a crow or a hawk was to grab a piece of flesh and fly "
"away."

# The verbs here are uncertain, and readings vary considerably, both here and in the other occurence in SN 19. Here the comm. glosses clearly in the sense of “pecking and clawing” and I think it’s best to just stick to that.
#. VAR: vissajjeyyuṃ → virājeyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:16.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kaṅkāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitaccheyyuṃ "
"vissajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Other vultures, crows, and hawks would keep chasing it, pecking and clawing."

msgctxt "mn54:16.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "mn54:16.4"
msgid ""
"sace so gijjho vā kaṅko vā kulalo vā taṃ maṃsapesiṃ na khippameva "
"paṭinissajjeyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā "
"dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If that vulture, crow, or hawk doesn’t quickly let go of that piece of "
"flesh, wouldn’t that result in death or deadly suffering for them?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:16.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.365"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:16.6"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:16.7"
msgid ""
"‘maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:16.8"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā "
"taṃ abhinivajjetvā yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso "
"lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:17.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ ādāya paṭivātaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose a person carrying a blazing grass torch was to walk against the "
"wind."

msgctxt "mn54:17.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

#. VAR: daheyya aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ → daheyya. aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ (bj, pts1) | ḍaheyya … (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn54:17.3"
msgid ""
"sace so puriso taṃ ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ na khippameva paṭinissajjeyya tassa sā "
"ādittā tiṇukkā hatthaṃ vā daheyya bāhuṃ vā daheyya aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā "
"aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ daheyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā "
"dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If that person doesn’t quickly let go of that blazing grass torch, wouldn’t "
"they burn their hands or arm or other limb, resulting in death or deadly "
"suffering for them?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:17.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:17.5"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:17.6"
msgid ""
"‘tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:17.7"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā … pe … tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:18.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, gahapati, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā, pūrā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ "
"vītadhūmānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, full "
"of glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked."

msgctxt "mn54:18.2"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikkūlo."
msgstr ""
"Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, "
"who wants to be happy and recoils from pain."

msgctxt "mn54:18.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ dve balavanto purisā nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuṃ upakaḍḍheyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then two strong men would grab them by the arms and drag them towards the "
"pit of glowing coals."

msgctxt "mn54:18.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "mn54:18.5"
msgid "api nu so puriso iticiticeva kāyaṃ sannāmeyyā”ti?"
msgstr "Wouldn’t that person writhe and struggle to and fro?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:18.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:18.7"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:18.8"
msgid ""
"“Viditañhi, bhante, tassa purisassa imañcāhaṃ aṅgārakāsuṃ papatissāmi, "
"tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchissāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti."
msgstr ""
"For that person knows: ‘If I fall in that pit of glowing coals, that’d "
"result in my death or deadly pain.’” …"

msgctxt "mn54:18.9"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:18.10"
msgid ""
"‘aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:18.11"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā … pe … tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:19.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso supinakaṃ passeyya ārāmarāmaṇeyyakaṃ "
"vanarāmaṇeyyakaṃ bhūmirāmaṇeyyakaṃ pokkharaṇirāmaṇeyyakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose a person was to see delightful parks, woods, meadows, and lotus "
"ponds in a dream."

# Reading passeyya.
#. VAR: paṭipasseyya → passeyya (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:19.2"
msgid "So paṭibuddho na kiñci paṭipasseyya."
msgstr "But when they woke they couldn’t see them at all. …"

msgctxt "mn54:19.3"
msgid "Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:19.4"
msgid ""
"‘supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:19.5"
msgid "tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.366"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
#. VAR: yānaṃ vā → yānaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: poriseyyaṃ → poroseyyaṃ (bj, pts1, mr) | oropeyya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn54:20.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso yācitakaṃ bhogaṃ yācitvā yānaṃ vā poriseyyaṃ "
"pavaramaṇikuṇḍalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a man had borrowed some goods—a gentleman’s carriage and fine "
"jewelled earrings—"

# The sutta is set at Apana.
msgctxt "mn54:20.2"
msgid ""
"So tehi yācitakehi bhogehi purakkhato parivuto antarāpaṇaṃ paṭipajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"and preceded and surrounded by these he proceeded through the middle of "
"Āpaṇa."

msgctxt "mn54:20.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When people saw him they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn54:20.4"
msgid "‘bhogī vata bho puriso, evaṃ kira bhogino bhogāni bhuñjantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This must be a wealthy man! For that’s how the wealthy enjoy their wealth.’"

msgctxt "mn54:20.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sāmikā yattha yattheva passeyyuṃ tattha tattheva sāni hareyyuṃ."
msgstr "But when the owners saw him, they’d take back what was theirs."

msgctxt "mn54:20.6"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, alaṃ nu kho tassa purisassa aññathattāyā”ti?"
msgstr "What do you think? Would that be enough for that man to get upset?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:20.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:20.8"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:20.9"
msgid "“Sāmino hi, bhante, sāni harantī”ti."
msgstr "Because the owners took back what was theirs.” …"

msgctxt "mn54:20.10"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:20.11"
msgid ""
"‘yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn54:20.12"
msgid "tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.367"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:21.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre tibbo vanasaṇḍo."
msgstr "“Suppose there was a dark forest grove not far from a town or village."

#. VAR: upapannaphalo → uppannaphalo (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn54:21.2"
msgid ""
"Tatrassa rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, na cassu kānici phalāni "
"bhūmiyaṃ patitāni."
msgstr ""
"And there was a tree laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit had fallen to "
"the ground."

msgctxt "mn54:21.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya phalatthiko phalagavesī phalapariyesanaṃ caramāno."
msgstr "And along came a person in need of fruit, wandering in search of fruit."

msgctxt "mn54:21.4"
msgid ""
"So taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā taṃ rukkhaṃ passeyya sampannaphalañca "
"upapannaphalañca."
msgstr ""
"Having plunged deep into that forest grove, they’d see that tree laden with "
"fruit."

msgctxt "mn54:21.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn54:21.6"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, natthi ca kānici phalāni "
"bhūmiyaṃ patitāni."
msgstr ""
"‘That tree is laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit has fallen to the "
"ground."

#. VAR: ārohituṃ → āruhituṃ (bj) | abhiruyhituṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn54:21.7"
msgid "Jānāmi kho panāhaṃ rukkhaṃ ārohituṃ."
msgstr "But I know how to climb a tree."

msgctxt "mn54:21.8"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ rukkhaṃ ārohitvā yāvadatthañca khādeyyaṃ ucchaṅgañca "
"pūreyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I climb the tree, eat as much as I like, then fill my pouch?’"

msgctxt "mn54:21.9"
msgid "So taṃ rukkhaṃ ārohitvā yāvadatthañca khādeyya ucchaṅgañca pūreyya."
msgstr "And that’s what they’d do."

#. VAR: kuṭhāriṃ → kudhāriṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:21.10"
msgid ""
"Atha dutiyo puriso āgaccheyya phalatthiko phalagavesī phalapariyesanaṃ "
"caramāno tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya."
msgstr ""
"And along would come a second person in need of fruit, wandering in search "
"of fruit, carrying a sharp axe."

msgctxt "mn54:21.11"
msgid ""
"So taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā taṃ rukkhaṃ passeyya sampannaphalañca "
"upapannaphalañca."
msgstr ""
"Having plunged deep into that forest grove, they’d see that tree laden with "
"fruit."

msgctxt "mn54:21.12"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn54:21.13"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, natthi ca kānici phalāni "
"bhūmiyaṃ patitāni."
msgstr ""
"‘That tree is laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit has fallen to the "
"ground."

msgctxt "mn54:21.14"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ jānāmi rukkhaṃ ārohituṃ."
msgstr "But I don’t know how to climb a tree."

msgctxt "mn54:21.15"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ rukkhaṃ mūlato chetvā yāvadatthañca khādeyyaṃ ucchaṅgañca "
"pūreyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I chop this tree down at the root, eat as much as I like, then "
"fill my pouch?’"

msgctxt "mn54:21.16"
msgid "So taṃ rukkhaṃ mūlatova chindeyya."
msgstr "And so they’d chop the tree down at the root."

msgctxt "mn54:21.17"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

#. VAR: amuko yo → asu yo (bj, pts1) | amuko (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn54:21.18"
msgid ""
"amuko yo so puriso paṭhamaṃ rukkhaṃ ārūḷho sace so na khippameva oroheyya "
"tassa so rukkho papatanto hatthaṃ vā bhañjeyya pādaṃ vā bhañjeyya aññataraṃ "
"vā aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ bhañjeyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā "
"nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If the first person, who climbed the tree, doesn’t quickly come down, when "
"that tree fell wouldn’t they break their hand or arm or other limb, "
"resulting in death or deadly suffering for them?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:21.19"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:21.20"
msgid "“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "“In the same way, a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "mn54:21.21"
msgid ""
"‘rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘With the simile of the fruit tree the Buddha said that sensual pleasures "
"give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all "
"the more full of drawbacks.’"

msgctxt "mn54:21.22"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā "
"taṃ abhinivajjetvā yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso "
"lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""
"Having truly seen this with proper understanding, they reject equanimity "
"based on diversity and develop only the equanimity based on unity, where all "
"kinds of grasping to the world’s carnal delights cease without anything left "
"over."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:22.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,"
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple recollects their many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "mn54:22.2"
msgid ""
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a "
"hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world "
"contracting, many eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world "
"contracting and evolving. … They recollect their many kinds of past lives, "
"with features and details."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:23.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati "
"cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … "
"yathākammūpage satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, sees sentient "
"beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and "
"ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings "
"are reborn according to their deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:24.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due "
"to the ending of defilements."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:25.1"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, gahapati, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ "
"vohārasamucchedo hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how there is the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect "
"in the noble one’s training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.368"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:25.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "mn54:25.3"
msgid ""
"yathā ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hoti, "
"api nu tvaṃ evarūpaṃ vohārasamucchedaṃ attani samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard yourself as having cut off judgments in a way comparable to "
"the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s "
"training?”"

msgctxt "mn54:25.4"
msgid ""
"“Ko cāhaṃ, bhante, ko ca ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ "
"vohārasamucchedo."
msgstr ""
"“Who am I compared to one who has cut off judgments in each and every "
"respect in the noble one’s training?"

msgctxt "mn54:25.5"
msgid ""
"Ārakā ahaṃ, bhante, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ "
"vohārasamucchedā."
msgstr "I am far from that."

msgctxt "mn54:25.6"
msgid ""
"Mayañhi, bhante, pubbe aññatitthiye paribbājake anājānīyeva samāne ājānīyāti "
"amaññimha, anājānīyeva samāne ājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojimha, anājānīyeva samāne "
"ājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapimha;"
msgstr ""
"Sir, I used to think that the wanderers following other paths were "
"thoroughbreds, and I fed them and treated them accordingly, but they were "
"not actually thoroughbreds."

msgctxt "mn54:25.7"
msgid ""
"bhikkhū pana mayaṃ, bhante, ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyāti amaññimha, "
"ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojimha, ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyaṭhāne "
"ṭhapimha;"
msgstr ""
"I thought that the mendicants were not thoroughbreds, and I fed them and "
"treated them accordingly, but they actually were thoroughbreds."

msgctxt "mn54:25.8"
msgid ""
"idāni pana mayaṃ, bhante, aññatitthiye paribbājake anājānīyeva samāne "
"anājānīyāti jānissāma, anājānīyeva samāne anājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojessāma, "
"anājānīyeva samāne anājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapessāma."
msgstr ""
"But now I shall understand that the wanderers following other paths are not "
"actually thoroughbreds, and I will feed them and treat them accordingly."

msgctxt "mn54:25.9"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū pana mayaṃ, bhante, ājānīyeva samāne ājānīyāti jānissāma, ājānīyeva "
"samāne ājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojessāma, ājānīyeva samāne ājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapessāma."
msgstr ""
"And I shall understand that the mendicants actually are thoroughbreds, and I "
"will feed them and treat them accordingly."

msgctxt "mn54:25.10"
msgid ""
"Ajanesi vata me, bhante, bhagavā samaṇesu samaṇappemaṃ, samaṇesu "
"samaṇappasādaṃ, samaṇesu samaṇagāravaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha has inspired me to have love, confidence, and respect for "
"ascetics!"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn54:26.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "mn54:26.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya, ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavatā "
"anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "mn54:26.3"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn54:26.4"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn54:26.5"
msgid "Potaliyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
